> removing. Some carbs will hit on the alt also , but can be  bent or lever reversed
> to fit. Do away with the voltage regulator and wire the  big wires together
> and the 2 smaller wires together.  later  mark d

Ah, yes, I forgot about the fuel pump issue.  The alternator will fit over
any fuel pump, but the older style pump cannot be removed with the
alternator in place, leading to a real hassle eventually.  Best to replace
the pump with the angled style pump and the correct shorter pushrod.
